==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recast
<hw>Re*cast"</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧*k⟦adot⟧st")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To throw again.</def> <rj><au>Florio.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To mold anew; to cast anew; to throw into a new form
or shape; to reconstruct; <as>as, to <ex>recast</ex> cannon; to
<ex>recast</ex> an argument or a play.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To compute, or cast up, a second time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recche</ent>⟦br⟧
